                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18491029-name-1127" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18491029-name-1127" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18491029-name-1127" type="surname" value="BONUS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18491029-name-1127" type="given" value="JOHN COLLETT"></interp>JOHN COLLETT BONUS</persName>
                  </hi>. I a man ironmonger, of Warrington-place, Wands<lb></lb>worth—the prisoner has had goods of me for Mr. Forster, of the Three Goats, who has paid for them; the last time was ten or twelve months ago—he came to me on 14th July, and asked for some bolts and screws for Mr. Forster—I let him have them, supposing he was sent by Mr. Forster—I after<lb></lb>wards saw the prisoner at Mr. Forster's, and asked him how he could think of coming to me and getting <hi rend="italic">goods</hi> when <hi rend="italic">he</hi> was not sent—he said, "I know I have done wrong; I will pay you."</p>
